{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/3/comments/2177515.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/3/_/diff#comment-2177515"}}, "parent": {"id": 2177339, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/3/comments/2177339.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/3/_/diff#comment-2177339"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 3, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/3.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/3"}}, "title": "Initial complete version"}, "content": {"raw": "That was excellent intuition, recompiling protobuf with `--c++11` fixed the build, though it gave an ominous warning:\n~~~\nWarning: ignition-transport dependency boost was built with a different C++ standard\nlibrary (libstdc++ from clang). This could cause problems at runtime.\n~~~\nboost is a transitive dependency from robot_msgs. I think it would be best to keep robot_msgs from depending on boost ([issue here](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/robot_msgs/issue/3/remove-boost-dependency))", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>That was excellent intuition, recompiling protobuf with <code>--c++11</code> fixed the build, though it gave an ominous warning:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">Warning</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ignition</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">transport</span> <span class=\"n\">dependency</span> <span class=\"n\">boost</span> <span class=\"n\">was</span> <span class=\"n\">built</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">different</span> <span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">++</span> <span class=\"n\">standard</span>\n<span class=\"n\">library</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">libstdc</span><span class=\"o\">++</span> <span class=\"n\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">clang</span><span class=\"o\">).</span> <span class=\"n\">This</span> <span class=\"n\">could</span> <span class=\"n\">cause</span> <span class=\"n\">problems</span> <span class=\"n\">at</span> <span class=\"n\">runtime</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>boost is a transitive dependency from robot_msgs. I think it would be best to keep robot_msgs from depending on boost (<a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://bitbucket.org/osrf/robot_msgs/issue/3/remove-boost-dependency\" rel=\"nofollow\">issue here</a>)</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-06-18T23:07:55.079034+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": "2014-06-18T23:07:55.088783+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 2177515}